# Always deploy on `opus-4.8`

The owner only sees the **live site** (GitHub Pages from `opus-4.8`). Unpushed or branch-only work is invisible.

## When work is done

1. **Commit + push** the feature branch (if you used one).
2. **Merge into `opus-4.8`** — fast-forward or merge; never leave verified work stranded on a side branch.
3. **Push `origin opus-4.8`** — this triggers the Pages deploy workflow.
4. **Confirm deploy** — `gh run list --branch opus-4.8` should show a successful "Deploy to GitHub Pages" run.

## Release trinity (when shipping)

All three together: bump `src/changelog.ts`, update `<span class="version">` in `index.html`, patch version only.

## Do not

- Stop at "PR opened" or "pushed feature branch" without merging to `opus-4.8`.
- Ask the owner to deploy unless merge is genuinely blocked (conflict you cannot resolve).

## If the owner says "deploy" / "push to opus"

Merge to `opus-4.8`, push, wait for deploy green — no extra confirmation needed.
